Job Description
This Staff Kubernetes Administrator role is critical to our team’s success. If you are passionate about Kubernetes, cloud technologies, and mentoring others
in a fast-paced environment, we encourage you to apply and help us drive our infrastructure to the next level.
In this role, you will establish Kubernetes best practices and processes as we build out this capability. You will work closely with software development
and product teams to deploy and support Kubernetes clusters on-premises and in the cloud (GCP). You will ensure our Kubernetes environments are
secure, performant, and aligned with business needs. Additionally, you will mentor junior administrators and help develop the team’s Kubernetes skill set
and operational practices.
Responsibilities
Design, deploy, and maintain Kubernetes clusters in on-premises environments and in Google Cloud (GKE), ensuring scalable and reliable
infrastructure.
Lead the migration of containerized workloads from on-premises Kubernetes to GKE, with minimal downtime and optimal performance.
Implement and enforce Kubernetes security best practices, including RBAC access controls, network policies, secrets management, and vulnerability
scanning.
Architect and support microservices and serverless applications on Kubernetes using cloud-native patterns and tooling.
Develop and maintain Infrastructure as Code (IaC) using tools like Terraform and Helm, and employ GitOps workflows for automated deployments.
Monitor and optimize cluster performance and availability, using observability tools (Prometheus, Grafana, ELK/EFK, etc.), and ensure high uptime
through auto-scaling and resiliency best practices.
Participate in incident response and troubleshooting to quickly resolve issues across the Kubernetes stack (applications, containers, nodes) and
perform root cause analysis.
Mentor and coach junior administrators and engineers, sharing Kubernetes best practices and fostering a culture of continuous learning.
Collaborate cross-functionally with development, security, and other infrastructure teams to ensure Kubernetes platform alignment with application
needs and security standards.
Document configurations, procedures, and processes for Kubernetes environments to support knowledge transfer and consistency.
Required Qualifications & Skills
8-10 years of IT infrastructure experience, including 4+ years managing production Kubernetes clusters.
Expertise in Linux systems administration, especially Ubuntu and Red Hat (or CentOS) systems, including strong shell scripting and system
troubleshooting skills.
Strong knowledge of container networking and services – e.g., CNI plugins, ingress controllers, DNS, load balancing, and service mesh (Istio or
similar).
Deep understanding of Kubernetes security models and best practices (RBAC, network policies, CIS benchmarks, etc.).
Proficiency with Infrastructure as Code tools (Terraform, Helm) and experience with CI/CD pipelines and GitOps workflows for Kubernetes
deployments.
Experience with monitoring and logging tools for Kubernetes (Prometheus, Grafana, Fluentd/ELK or similar) and the ability to interpret metrics/logs
to maintain system health.
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to work collaboratively and explain complex concepts to various stakeholders.
Strong problem-solving abilities and capability to work independently, managing priorities in a dynamic environment.
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related field (or equivalent experience).
Willingness to support off-hours needs (occasional meetings with offshore teams) and travel if required.
Desired Skills
Certifications: Relevant industry certifications such as Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA) or CKS, and cloud certifications (Google Cloud
Professional Architect, GKE specialization) or Linux certifications (RHCSA/RHCE).
Hybrid/Cloud Experience: Experience with hybrid cloud or multi-cluster Kubernetes environments and cloud networking.
Security & Automation Tools: Familiarity with container security platforms (e.g., Aqua, Prisma, Sysdig) and configuration management/automation
tools (Ansible, Puppet, Chef, Python/Bash scripting).
Methodologies: Exposure to IT service management (ITIL practices) and Agile/Scrum development methodologies.
Innovative Mindset: A security-first and automation-first mindset; enthusiasm for






